A 73-year-old man was injured when he lost control of his
car while trying to avoid crashing into a gas bottle on the M2 in Germiston. Netcare 911 spokesperson Shawn Herbst said the incident happened
around 22H49 on Sunday night. According to Herbst reports from the scene indicate that the
driver SUV lost control when he tried to avoid a gas bottle which was on his
lane. “In the process the vehicle crashed into the barrier and
rolled. The driver, a 73-year-old male sustained minor injuries and was treated
on scene,” Herbst said. Herbst said once stabilised the patient was transported to
hospital for further treatment. 